<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
<meta charset="UTF-8" />
<meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0"/>
<title>Vote Britain Manifesto</title>

<style>
  :root {
    --dark: #0b1f3a;
    --accent: #ffcc00;
    --bg: #f5f7fb;
  }

  body {
    margin: 0;
    font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
    background: var(--bg);
    color: #222;
  }

  header {
    background: linear-gradient(135deg, var(--dark), #123a63);
    color: white;
    text-align: center;
    padding: 50px 20px;
  }

  header h1 {
    margin: 0;
    font-size: 3rem;
  }

  header p {
    margin-top: 10px;
    opacity: 0.9;
  }

  /* VALUES BOX */
  .values {
    max-width: 900px;
    margin: 30px auto;
    background: white;
    padding: 20px;
    border-radius: 12px;
    box-shadow: 0 5px 20px rgba(0,0,0,0.08);
  }

  .values h2 {
    color: var(--dark);
    margin-bottom: 10px;
  }

  /* BUTTON LIST */
  .container {
    max-width: 900px;
    margin: auto;
    padding: 20px;
  }

  .btn {
    width: 100%;
    background: white;
    border: none;
    padding: 15px;
    margin: 10px 0;
    text-align: left;
    font-size: 1.1rem;
    border-radius: 10px;
    cursor: pointer;
    box-shadow: 0 3px 10px rgba(0,0,0,0.08);
    transition: 0.3s;
  }

  .btn:hover {
    background: #f0f4ff;
  }

  .panel {
    max-height: 0;
    overflow: hidden;
    transition: max-height 0.5s ease;
    background: white;
    border-radius: 0 0 10px 10px;
    margin-bottom: 10px;
    padding: 0 15px;
  }

  .panel p, .panel li {
    line-height: 1.6;
  }

  .panel ul {
    padding-left: 20px;
  }

  .active + .panel {
    padding: 15px;
  }

  footer {
    text-align: center;
    padding: 30px;
    background: var(--dark);
    color: white;
    margin-top: 40px;
  }

</style>
</head>

<body>

<header>
  <h1>VOTE BRITAIN</h1>
  <p>Real Solutions. Respect for Britain. A Future That Works for Everyone.</p>
</header>

<!-- VALUES -->
<div class="values">
  <h2>Our Values</h2>
  <p>
    This manifesto is built on fairness, responsibility, opportunity, and national renewal.
    We believe government should serve people, protect communities, reward work, and act in the national interest with common sense and evidence-based decisions.
  </p>
</div>

<div class="container">

<button class="btn">Work, Tax & Living Standards</button>
<div class="panel">
  <ul>
    <li>Reduce tax on second jobs from 40% to 25%, with additional jobs untaxed.</li>
    <li>Fairer taxation for high earners with optional allocation of contributions.</li>
    <li>Expand flexible working patterns across sectors.</li>
    <li>Improve parental leave and childcare support.</li>
    <li>Flexible maternity and parental leave options.</li>
  </ul>
</div>

<button class="btn">Welfare Reform & Social Support</button>
<div class="panel">
  <ul>
    <li>Replace current welfare system with a redesigned fair support model.</li>
    <li>Strengthen safeguards for vulnerable claimants.</li>
    <li>Community contribution opportunities for unemployed (with exemptions).</li>
    <li>Rent and bill relief for single-adult households.</li>
    <li>Free menstrual products in public institutions.</li>
  </ul>
</div>

<button class="btn">Immigration & Borders</button>
<div class="panel">
  <ul>
    <li>End illegal entry settlement pathways and strengthen border security.</li>
    <li>Skills-based fast digital visa system.</li>
    <li>Time-limited visas based on contribution.</li>
    <li>Civic Integration Agreement covering language, work, and law.</li>
  </ul>
</div>

<button class="btn">Education & Youth Opportunity</button>
<div class="panel">
  <ul>
    <li>Reform GCSE structure and subject flexibility.</li>
    <li>Focus on creativity, problem-solving, and real-world skills.</li>
    <li>Community-based learning experiences.</li>
    <li>Replace Youth Parliament with elected Youth MPs.</li>
  </ul>
</div>

<button class="btn">Health, Safety & Work Conditions</button>
<div class="panel">
  <ul>
    <li>Legal workplace temperature safety thresholds.</li>
    <li>Stronger animal cruelty sentencing.</li>
    <li>Tougher antisocial behaviour enforcement.</li>
    <li>Corporate accountability reforms.</li>
  </ul>
</div>

<button class="btn">Housing & Communities</button>
<div class="panel">
  <ul>
    <li>National housing soundproofing standards.</li>
    <li>Faster antisocial behaviour response systems.</li>
    <li>Balanced tenant and landlord responsibility system.</li>
  </ul>
</div>

<button class="btn">Democracy & Public Power</button>
<div class="panel">
  <ul>
    <li>National consultations and public policy surveys.</li>
    <li>Greater citizen influence in tax allocation.</li>
    <li>Referendums on major national decisions.</li>
    <li>Strengthened petition system for accountability.</li>
  </ul>
</div>

<button class="btn">Culture & Community</button>
<div class="panel">
  <ul>
    <li>Christianity as cultural foundation with protected religious freedom.</li>
    <li>Annual national unity day.</li>
    <li>Stronger community participation.</li>
    <li>Reduced social isolation initiatives.</li>
  </ul>
</div>

<button class="btn">Governance & Reform</button>
<div class="panel">
  <ul>
    <li>Evidence-based “common sense” governance principle.</li>
    <li>Protections for long-serving public sector workers.</li>
    <li>Support for British citizens emigrating abroad.</li>
  </ul>
</div>

</div>

<footer>
  <h3>Vote Britain</h3>
  <p>Real Solutions. Strong Communities. A Better Future.</p>
</footer>

<script>
  const buttons = document.querySelectorAll(".btn");

  buttons.forEach(btn => {
    btn.addEventListener("click", () => {
      const panel = btn.nextElementSibling;

      if (panel.style.maxHeight) {
        panel.style.maxHeight = null;
      } else {
        panel.style.maxHeight = panel.scrollHeight + "px";
      }
    });
  });
</script>

</body>
</html>
